15. (1) Any settler who disobeys these rules or refuses to obey any
reasonable order given by the Manager of the corrective settlement shall
be subject to any one or more of the following penalties, —

a) A formal warning;

(b) Additional or more arduous work at the discretion of the Manager of the
corrective settlement;

c) reduced wages or loss of wages for work done;
